<TEXT>
former president reagan before he left office 
told congress that the united states would be unlikely to certify 
this year that pakistan does not possess a nuclear bomb the 
washington post reported 
the newspaper in its saturday editions said reagan certified 
last november that pakistan does not possess a nuclear explosive 
device but attached a letter to house speaker jim wright dtex 
saying the administration was nearing its limits of being able to 
continue making the certification 
the congress should be aware that as pakistans capabilities 
grow and if evidence about its activities continue to accumulate 
this process of annual certification will require the president to 
reach judgments about the status of pakistani nuclear activities 
that may be difficult or impossible to make with any degree of 
certainty the post quoted reagan as saying 
without certification required annually under the law pakistan 
will not be eligible to receive us economic and military aid 
beyond the current fiscal year which ends sept 30 
the reagan administration budget for fiscal year 1990 includes a 
request for 621 million in assistance to pakistan part of a 402 
billions sixyear package 
the post quoting unnamed congressional sources said reagan 
administration officials had told lawmakers privately that pakistan 
was so close to building a bomb that it had been a very close 
call in renewing the certification last november 
the newspaper said it was not known if president bush will accept 
its predecessors conclusion about pakistans nuclear capabilities 
although bush is known to be extremely concerned about the problem 
of nuclear weapons proliferation 
in his letter to wright the post said reagan said he had made 
his best judgment on the basis of available information to the 
us government based on the standard set by congress regarding the 
pakistani nuclear program 
the standard he said is whether pakistan possesses a nuclear 
explosive device not whether pakistan is attempting to develop or 
has developed various relevant capacities 
reagan said in the letter that the united states remained 
extremely troubled by the continuing risk of a nuclear arms race 
between pakistan and india the post said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

