<TEXT>
cambodian prime minister hun sen ended 
an unprecedented visit to thailand on friday declaring the 
killings must stop in his country 
hun sens visit to thailand which previously shunned his 
vietnamesebacked government and supports the guerrilla coalition 
fighting it is considered an important move to end the conflict 
we are starting to build a foundation said thai foreign 
policy adviser kraisak chunhavan 
hun sen said his trip was successful but he brushed aside 
reports that the visit at bangkoks invitation implies recognition 
of his government by thailand 
the question of recognition or nonrecognition does not matter 
the question is to stop the killing as soon as possible he said 
the unexpected talks reflects thailands worry that other parties 
that might not represent its interests are taking major initiatives 
on the cambodian issue 
in the past bangkok derided cambodias leaders as puppets of the 
vietnamese 
in new delhi india meanwhile vietnams foreign minister friday 
said cambodian peace talks in indonesia would be held as scheduled 
despite prince norodom sihanouks statement that he will not attend 
nguyen co thatch compared the peace talks beginning feb 19 with 
the final 15 minutes of a soccer match where everyone is trying to 
score a point if anyone misses the match it is his 
responsibility 
the match will continue i only hope prince sihanouk will 
change his stand thach told a news conference 
sihanouk said he will not come to the talks because hun sen has 
rejected his fivepoint cambodian peace plan 
the role of prince sihanouk is very important but he cannot 
decide everything thach said 
thach was in india along with nguyen van linh secretarygeneral 
of vietnams communist party who was the chief guest at indias 
republic day celebrations on thursday 
vietnamese troops invaded camdobia in late 1978 and installed a 
prohanoi government in phnom penh vietnam says it will pull out 
completely from cambodia by the end of 1990 or perhaps sooner if a 
political solution is reached 
the vietnamese are fighting a coalition of three major cambodian 
resistance groups the communist khmer rouge the noncommunist 
khmer peoples national liberation front of former cambodian prime 
minister son sann and followers of sihanouk 
the vietnamese invaded cambodia in 1978 to drive the khmer rouge 
from power from the 1975 takeover of the khmer rouge to its ouster 
an estimated 2 million of cambodias 8 million people died from 
khmer rouge executions famine and civil unrest 
</TEXT>
