deficiency syndrome in the united states as reported this week by 
the national centers for disease control 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
total cases reported since june 1981 84503 
cases year to date 1740 
total deaths 48222 or 57 percent of all cases 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
homosexual or bisexual males 51279 or 61 percent 
intravenous drug abusers 16597 or 20 percent 
homosexual male and drug abusers 5973 or 7 percent 
heterosexual cases 3669 or 4 percent 
transfusion or blood cases 2251 or 3 percent 
hemophilia patients 873 or 1 percent 
children of parents with aids or at risk 1065 or 1 percent 
undetermined transmission cause 2796 or 3 percent 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
childhood cases under age 13 1375 or 2 percent 
cases among whites 48541 or 57 percent 
cases among blacks 22472 or 27 percent 
cases among hispanics 12710 or 15 percent 
cases among asians or pacific islanders 499 or 1 percent 
cases among american indians or alaskan natives 90 or 0 percent 
 
note these statistics are through jan 23 and have been rounded 
to the nearest whole percent cumulative totals are for aids cases 
reported since june 1981 and include 75 cases subsequently found to 
have occurred prior to that date 
