<TEXT>
whats black and white and red all over made 
from puckered polyester stretch fabric and covered with starfish 
the winner of the ugliest tie in america contest of course 
this revolting piece of neckwear and 1400 other contest entries 
were on display thursday evening at the italian trade commission in 
new york which advertised the competition in esquire magazine as a 
way to promote a tasteful alternative silk designer ties in 
subdued colors imported from italy 
among the top 10 ugly ties brightly colored nylon and large 
geometric shapes were common the grand prizewinning black white 
and red number was submitted by 18yearold asim siddique of dallas 
who said he had a hard time choosing from his fathers large 
assortment of hideous neckwear 
i thought i had a pretty good shot at winning said siddique 
a freshman at collin county junior college reached at home by 
telephone once you see the collection you would think the odds 
are on your side 
siddique won 50 italian designer silk ties as grand prize and he 
plans to stick a few in his dads closet when hes not looking 
each of the 10 runnersup won 25 designer ties 
one of the runnersup geraldine friedman of upper montclair 
nj sent in a brown gold and silver tie bearing a design of 
medallions diamonds and black and white checks 
she said her husband wore it to their sons bar mitzvah 15 years 
ago but i doubt hes worn it since my husband has so many of 
these ugly ties that you cant believe 
among the other runnersup were a velour tie covered with 
multicolored hexagons submitted by kevin shippy of akron ohio and 
a greenandyellow number with large flowers of which the owner 
colin mackenzie of vancouver canada wrote i wore it with a pink 
shirt and love beads 
the neckwear that didnt win included ties bearing smile faces 
sailboats american flags pieces of a patchwork quilt peace signs 
and even a naked woman 
most of the ugly ties were also very wide five to six inches and 
more the ideal width for a tie these days according to the 
february issue of gentlemens quarterly is 3 to 3 inches 
italian trade commissioner mario costagna said that when he saw 
the winners i was about to faint he said he doubted there 
would be quite so many klunkers were the same contest held in italy 
costagna said americans bought more than 62 million worth of 
italian ties last year 
esquires editorinchief lee eisenberg said he made sure to 
wear a perfectly boring blackandwhite tie to the party 
announcing the winners he blamed the profusion of ugly ties not on 
their owners but on giftgivers 
looking at the hundreds of fashion disasters on display he said 
i find it kind of melancholy to me it represents 1200 sad 
fathers day mornings 
