news the school announced 
the gold baton the highest honor of the prestigious broadcast 
journalism awards was formally presented at a ceremony hosted by 
charles kuralt anchor of cbstvs sunday morning program 
other network television winners among the 13 news programs to 
capture silver batons at the 47th annual awards were cbs news for 
coverage of the persian gulf by allen pizzey nbc news for a 
conversation with mikhail gorbachev and abc news for nightline 
in the holy land the university said in a release 
the 60 minutes program was cited by the awards jurors for 
doing more than just establish the news magazine format for 
television 
in its 20year existence it has given more time in prime time 
to investigative pieces captivating features fascinating profiles 
and historic interviews than any other program in the history of 
television news the release said 
