states and puerto rico in 1988 with vandalism up 19 percent and 
harassment up 41 percent over 1987 the 1987 total was 1018 
last years figure was the highest of any of the past five years 
the number of incidents reached 1422 in 1982 the highest in the 10 
years the group has compiled the audit from reports by its regional 
offices and law enforcement officials 
among the incidents cited in the survey were the spraypainting 
of antisemitic and racist slogans at a jewish high school in 
doraville ga the explosion of a pipe bomb on the grounds of a 
florida synagogue and the arson of a synagogue in the new york city 
also mentioned in the report were desecrations of jewish 
cemeteries and 54 antisemitic incidents on 38 college campuses 
which included vandalism threats harassment and assault 
the report cited a november attack against a jewish university 
student in new york city as being among the most brutal assaults a 
gang of youths allegedly shouted antisemitic epithets as they beat 
robbed and stabbed the 19yearold who survived 
isnt it ironic that in our lifetime weve conquered space and 
even eradicated smallpox yet we have not developed a vaccine against 
the virus of hate said abraham foxman national director of the 
antidefamation league 
there were 117 incidents linked to palestinian unrest in israels 
west bank and gaza region foxman said he believes antisemites used 
the situation to carry out acts of hatred under the guise of a 
political conflict 
another 41 incidents were linked to the rise of socalled 
skinheads 
the skinhead subculture emerged in london as early as the 1960s 
but segments of the movement took on nazi overtones in 1985 and 
since have been supported by and associated with white supremacist 
groups 
the league said more than 60 antisemitic incidents were sparked 
by the observance of the 50th anniversary of kristallnacht the 
night of violence against jews in germany and austria that many 
believe marked the beginning of the holocaust 
new york led the nation with 208 incidents half of those in new 
york city california had 121 florida 89 and new jersey 67 there 
were no incidents reported in 10 states 
according to the survey 124 people were arrested for 
antisemitic acts in 1988 approximately 90 percent of whom were 
under 21 
it was a record year for harassment incidents against jewish 
institutions in the 10 years the survey has been taken the group 
reported 133 such cases up about 10 percent from previous years 
</TEXT>
