a special un envoy arrived friday from 
iran for talks with iraqi officials in an effort to get deadlocked 
persian gulf peace talks moving again un officials said 
jan eliasson arrived by helicopter from the southern port of 
basra after inspecting gulf ceasefire lines in the region the 
officials said iraqi television said he flew the full length of the 
disputed shatt alarab waterway 
asked whether he was bringing a new peace proposal eliasson 
said i just arrived and i really am not prepared to go into 
questions of that nature 
eliasson swedens un ambassador and secretarygeneral javier 
perez de cuellars special emissary planned to meet with iraqi 
foreign minister tariq aziz on saturday the officials said 
there were no immediate signs that either gulf war rival was 
prepared to soften its stand and enable the talks to resume 
unsponsored peace talks between iran and iraq began in geneva 
on aug 25 five days after a ceasefire took effect in the 
8yearold gulf war 
but the talks broke down immediately over the issue of troop 
withdrawals to prewar borders two further round of negotiations 
failed to make progress and no date has been set for them to resume 
eliasson began his mission in iran on jan 23 holding four days 
of talks with prime minister hussein musavi foreign minister ali 
akbar velayati and other officials 
he said before leaving tehran it is very important to create a 
new momentum to speed up the trend of future peace talks 
irans islamic republic news agency quoted eliasson as saying 
friday that his talks were useful and fruitful it had no 
details 
the news agency monitored in nicosia quoted musavi as blaming 
iraq for the deadlock by refusing to withdraw from territory that 
iran claims was captured by the iraqis in lastminute attacks before 
the ceasefire took effect 
velayati said that before the peace talks begin again 
arrangements should be made so that these talks result in the 
full and speedy execution of the security council resolution 
including its first clause that is the return of troops to the 
international boundary 
un security council resolution 598 which both nations have 
agreed to calls on iran and iraq to halt all military activities 
and honor the truce withdraw troops to prewar borders exchange 
about 100000 prisoners of war and start peace talks 
iran insists troop withdrawals must be the next stage in the 
peace process but iraq says it will not pull out its troops from 
the 259 square miles of occupied territory until iran gives up the 
right to search ships in the gulf for iraqbound war cargo 
the iranian news agency said eliasson earlier inspected the 
southern war front with deputy foreign minister mohammad javad 
lavasani 
it said the un envoy was taken to an area where iran said the 
iraqis captured several hundred iranians after the aug 20 
ceasefire and also was shown three burning oil wells that iran 
claimed were set ablaze by iraq 
