that came up during a visit to ethiopia last fall by an italian 
parliament delegation 
mengistu said that italy could have a role in settling the 
eritrean question said mrs boniver the italian parliament 
member and president of parliaments foreign affairs committee 
italy should take up this very serious offer and try to start 
negotiations either trilaterally or involving other countries 
said mrs boniver who visited eritrea briefly last year and plans 
to return with other parliament members this year 
on the military front the eritreans say they want to consolidate 
their victories of last spring in march eplf guerrillas broke 
through a 10yearold front south of their headquarters in nacfa and 
overran the governmentheld town of afabet capturing three soviet 
military advisers in the process 
since then rebels have carried out hitandrun raids on the 
naval bases at massawa and masab in a communique in midjanuary 
the eplf claimed to have killed more than 2000 ethiopian soldiers 
along the state road connecting asmara the provincial capital and 
massawa 
kinfe said the eplf has been entrenched for months around the 
ethiopianheld city of keren in northcentral eritrea and the group 
is expecting the government to launch an offensive soon to try to 
break the siege 
according to the military balance a survey published by the 
londonbased international institute for strategic studies the eplf 
has about 30000 fighters ethiopia has a 315000member military 
not including cuban soviet and east german advisers and technicians 
while the ethiopians have been armed by the soviets the rebels 
rely mostly with captured government equipment including t54 and 
t55 tanks and heavy artillery ethiopia controls the skies with 
sovietsupplied mig warplanes and helicopters 
