<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures on eritrea 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land eritrea is ethiopias northernmost province covering 
48000 square miles slightly larger than pennsylvania it is 
bordered by sudan to the north and west the former french colony of 
djibouti to the southeast and the red sea forms its 625mile eastern 
border without eritrea ethiopia would be landlocked the territory 
has the only nonarab access to the red sea assab and massawa are 
its major seaports and asmara ethiopias second largest town is 
its capital 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people eritreas 35 million people speak nine languages 
and are nearly evenly divided between moslems and christians eighty 
percent of the people are rural and 30 percent of them are nomads 
secessionist rebels claim 500000 are refugees in neighboring sudan 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy before the war asmara was the industrial center of 
ethiopia mineral resources include gold iron and copper but they 
have not been exploited because of the war traces of oil also have 
been found offshore but the war has prevented further exploration 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history for most of its 3000year history eritrea has been 
coveted by foreign powers because of its strategic geographic 
position the region fought off invaders for centuries before the 
ottoman empire established a foothold on the coast in 1557 three 
hundred years later egypt occupied the eastern and western 
lowlands european domination came in 1891 when italy colonized the 
entire region and gave it the name eritrea derived from the ancient 
greek name for the red sea during world war ii italian forces of 
dictator benito mussolini used eritrea as a staging area for the 
invasion of ethiopia allied armies took eritrea in 1941 and for the 
next 11 years it was under british military administration eritrean 
leaders pushed for independence but ethiopia yearning for an 
access to the red sea received the strong backing of the united 
states and in 1952 eritrea was federated as an autonomous state with 
ethiopia on sept 1 1961 the eritrean liberation front was formed 
and civil war began on nov 14 1962 ethiopia abolished the 
federation and its armies occupied eritrea 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

