concerning insider trading since strengthened swiss legislation took 
effect last july 1 part of the legislations aim was to avoid past 
tension with us authorities in international probes 
under a swissus treaty judicial assistance can only be 
granted when alleged offenses are criminal in both countries 
fridays justice ministry statement noted that france to date has 
not asked for swiss judicial aid 
