<TEXT>
the chicago mercantile exchange said friday that 
its plans for a computerized worldwide trading system havent been 
stalled by the spreading scandal of a federal probe of suspected 
fraudulent futures trading 
implementation of the system known as globex is a key element 
in the exchanges attempts to conduct afterhours global futures 
trading at the same time some observers believe electronic trading 
systems in general cut the opportunities for fraud 
globex is on track and weve had as much interest as weve ever 
had said merc spokesman andrew yemma 
the merc and the chicago board of trade the nations largest 
commodities exchanges are targets of a twoyear federal probe in 
which fbi agents posed as traders and secretly taperecorded 
conversation on the trading floor 
some commodities market analysts have pointed to increased 
computerization as a means to curb fraud and profit skimming by 
floor traders under the open outcry system now used in the pits 
traders shout and use hand signals to arrange trades making it 
difficult to detect improper activity 
the globex system will have an almostperfect audit trail 
yemma said 
globex a project of the merc and reuters america inc is 
scheduled to come on line this fall with limited trading between new 
york and chicago full worldwide trading is to begin in 1990 yemma 
said 
the system would be activated at 6 pm the merc closes at 315 
pm cst and trade electronically with futures markets on other 
continents until 6 am with the merc reopening at 720 am cst 
with globex merc trading will be conducted nearly 20 hours a day 
the network would link investors in north america europe and 
asia for trading of futures and options contracts on currency 
futures including the british pound the west german mark the 
swiss and french francs australian and canadian dollars and the 
japanese yen 
the new york mercantile exchange voted thursday to join globex a 
move yemma called a big boost for the chicago exchange 
yemma labeled as completely erroneous reporters that several 
european financial institutions backed away from involvement in the 
network because of the ongoing federal investigation of the merc and 
the board of trade revealed last week 
the commodity futures trading commission the independent federal 
agency that regulates the industry must approve the system before 
it can begin operations 
under federal trading rules brokers are required to record 
transactions to the nearest minute timing is critical because of 
rapid price changes 
the new system will automatically record trade times to the 
nearest second even though globex only operates when the floor pits 
are closed 
critics including the rival board of trade say the system and 
computerized trading in general may make the markets vulnerable to 
computer hackers 
were not saying its completely foolproof said yemma 
were trying to thwart any kind of illegal activity we can think 
of 
last september the board of trade issued a 51page statement 
condemning globex 
were not against computerized trading per se bot spokesman 
mark prout said friday but we dont think it covers all the 
routes of possible manipulation 
in addition to the hacker threat prout said the system still 
would allow prearranged fraudulent trades 
we think the system should be perfectedand debugged before 
it could be considered said prout 
he said he doesnt foresee using globex even if it proves 
successful at the merc noting the bot already has a session from 5 
pm to 830 pm to provide access to overseas markets 
</TEXT>
