ended dec 31 were 145 million or 379 per share on revenue of 
43 billion compared with earnings of 93 million or 232 per 
share and revenue of 36 billion in the same period in 1987 
in a reversal of 1987s experience earnings expanded robustly in 
the combat aircraft segment largely because production costs were 
lower 
the division had difficulties in 1987 bringing out new models of 
the f15 and fa18 
most of these difficulties had been resolved by the fourth 
quarter of 1988 with a strongly positive effect on earnings the 
company stated 
