<TEXT>
bullish us economic indicators sent gold futures prices 
plummeting in trading friday at the new york commodity exchange and 
silver prices followed suit 
on other markets copper cattle and heating oil futures prices 
rallied pork prices were mixed grain soybean and crude oil prices 
were mostly lower and unleaded gasoline prices declined 
the government reported that the gross national product rose 38 
percent last year the best showing in four years 
the gnp report along with the tremendous strength of the 
dollar defuses inflationary pressure and thats what fuels 
precious metals said bette raptopoulous a metals analyst with 
prudentialbache securities inc in new york 
gold prices settled 690 to 940 lower with the contract for 
delivery in february at 39610 a troy ounce silver prices were 
221 cents to 246 cents lower with the february contract at 588 a 
troy ounce 
copper futures rallied on confirmation of a strike at a major 
refinery in mexico ms raptopoulous said 
traders bought copper futures contracts on expectations that the 
walkout will result in a tightening of copper supplies 
copper prices were 340 cents lower to 310 cents higher with 
the contract for delivery in february at 151 a pound 
cattle futures rallied sharply bolstered by agriculture 
department cattleonfeed figures released after the close of 
trading thursday 
the quarterly report showed that the number of cattle on the 
nations feed lots those to be fattened for slaughter increased 
only 5 percent in december 1988 over the same month in 1987 
the market had factored in about a 10 percent increase and 
the lower figure reported by the usda encouraged buying of cattle 
futures analysts said 
further support came from the approach of february declared by 
the industry as national meat month 
retailers have a tendency to promote beef a little more 
aggressively during the month which tightens supplies and helps 
account for the rise in futures prices analysts said 
pork prices were mixed under pressure from weak spot prices and 
other negative fundamentals but the strength in the cattle market 
kept the pork complex from plunging analysts noted 
live cattle settled 30 cent to 140 cents higher with the 
